  "educational_objective": "Friend play is messy but words help — stories about friends, sharing, feeling left out, saying sorry and turn-taking. Not basic emotion labelling (28–30m) or my-version worry retelling (31–33m).",
  "age_stage_nuance": "At nearly three, parallel play is giving way to friend preferences, toy rows and three-way jealousy. Books should model social repair and turn-taking rules, not name emotions in isolation.",
  "what_to_look_for": "Concrete friend-play plots; sharing/turn-taking/sorry/left-out themes; read-aloud length under ten minutes; UK paperback/board availability via publisher or Bookshop/Waterstones; age ranges that overlap 34–36m (e.g. Ages 2–5), not reading-age 4–8 only.",
  "what_to_avoid": "Colour Monster as a fresh buy; KS2 poetry; abstract metaphor; separation-anxiety-only titles; Amazon-primary ASINs that 404; publisher 3+ or 5–7-only pitches that fail the band age gate; duplicate Big Bright Feelings worry books from 31–33m.",
